Possible methods include: Levonorgestrel IUD, copper IUD, implants, LAM, oral contraceptive pills, sterilization, tubal ligation	

Note: LAM is an effective method for breastfeeding women who are amenorrhoeic and their infant < 6 months of age; 

Breastfeeding women < 6 weeks postpartum are generally advised not to use injectables and should not use combined hormonal contraceptive (CHC); 

Breastfeeding women ≥ 6 weeks can use injectables without restriction; Breastfeeding women ≥ 6 weeks to < 6 months postpartum (primarily breastfeeding) generally should not use CHCs unless other more appropriate methods are not available or acceptable (16).
